solution:
According to de-Broglie wavelength equation,

$$

\lambda=\frac{h}{m v} \Rightarrow \lambda \propto \frac{1}{v}

$$

According to photoelectric effect,

$$

\begin{array}{l}

\mathrm{hv}-\mathrm{hv}_{0}=\frac{1}{2} \mathrm{mv}^{2} ; \mathrm{v}-\mathrm{v}_{0}=\frac{1}{2}=\frac{\mathrm{mv}^{2}}{\mathrm{~h}} \\

\mathrm{v}-\mathrm{v}_{0} \propto \mathrm{v}^{2} \\

\mathrm{v} \propto\left(\mathrm{v}-\mathrm{v}_{0}\right)^{1 / 2} \\

\therefore \quad \lambda \propto \frac{1}{\left(\mathrm{v}-\mathrm{v}_{0}\right)^{1 / 2}}

\end{array}

$$
